# HR Frontend — Master Rules

This file is the single source of truth for all frontend development decisions.
Read it fully before writing any code, creating any file, or making any API call.

---

## 1. Project Identity

- **Framework:** Next.js (App Router) + React + TypeScript
- **Style:** Tailwind CSS v4 — RTL, Arabic-first (Cairo font)
- **Server state:** TanStack Query v5
- **Tables:** TanStack Table v8
- **Forms:** React Hook Form + Zod
- **UI state:** Zustand
- **UI components:** Radix UI / shadcn
- **Backend:** NestJS REST API — separate project
- **Language:** Arabic-first UI, English code

---

## 2. Backend API Contract

### 2.1 Base URL & Auth

Every request must include:
```
Authorization: Bearer <access_token>
```
Set this once in the Axios instance interceptor. Never set it per-request.
The token is a JWT with payload: `{ sub, email, tv, iat, exp }`.
There is no refresh token. On logout the server invalidates the token by incrementing `tokenVersion`.

### 2.2 Standard Response Shapes

**Every** endpoint returns one of these three shapes. No exceptions.

```typescript
// Single item or action response
interface ApiResponse<T> {
  status: number;
  message: string;
  data: T | null;
  error: null;
}

// Paginated list response
interface PaginatedResponse<T> {
  status: number;
  message: string;
  data: {
    items: T[];
    pagination: {
      page: number;       // current page
      limit: number;      // items per page
      total: number;      // total items count
      totalPages: number;
    };
  };
  error: null;
}

// Error response
interface ApiErrorResponse {
  status: number;
  message: string;
  data: null;
  error: {
    code: string;                    // e.g. "BadRequestException"
    details?: string | string[];     // validation messages
  };
}
```

Always use optional chaining when accessing response data:
```typescript
const items = response?.data?.items ?? [];
const pagination = response?.data?.pagination;
const record = response?.data;
```

### 2.3 Pagination

- Type: **page / limit** (not cursor-based)
- Default page: `1`
- Default limit: `200`
- Query params: `?page=1&limit=200`
- Sorting: **NOT standardized** — hardcoded per endpoint on the backend. Do not add sort UI unless you confirm the specific endpoint supports it.

### 2.4 Filtering by Module

Always pass these filters as query params when available:

