## 4. Permission System

### 4.1 Permission Format

All permissions follow: `<module>.<resource>.<action>`

```
hr.employees.read       hr.employees.create    hr.employees.update    hr.employees.delete
hr.leaves.read          hr.leaves.create       hr.leaves.update       hr.leaves.delete       hr.leaves.approve
hr.attendance.read      hr.attendance.create   hr.attendance.update   hr.attendance.delete
hr.contracts.read       hr.contracts.create    hr.contracts.update    hr.contracts.delete
hr.discipline.read      hr.discipline.create   hr.discipline.update   hr.discipline.delete
hr.recruitment.read     hr.recruitment.create  hr.recruitment.update  hr.recruitment.delete
```

### 4.2 Permission Source

Fetched once after login from `GET /auth/access-profile`.
Stored in Zustand auth store. Never refetched per component.

The response provides:
```typescript
permissions: string[]         // granted permissions
deniedPermissions: string[]   // explicitly denied — always takes priority over permissions
```

A permission present in both arrays is **DENIED**.

### 4.3 useCan Hook

Location: `src/hooks/usePermission.ts`

```typescript
export function useCan() {
  const { permissions, deniedPermissions } = useAuthStore();
  return (permission: string): boolean =>
    !deniedPermissions.includes(permission) && permissions.includes(permission);
}
```

### 4.4 UI Enforcement

```tsx
const can = useCan();

// Hide element — preferred
{can('hr.employees.create') && <Button>إضافة موظف</Button>}

// Disable element — only when hiding is not appropriate
<Button disabled={!can('hr.employees.update')}>تعديل</Button>

// Page-level guard
if (!can('hr.employees.read')) redirect('/unauthorized');

// Reusable gate component
<PermissionGate permission="hr.employees.delete">
  <DeleteButton />
</PermissionGate>
```

### 4.5 Table Row Actions

Always filter actions by permission. Never show disabled actions in a dropdown:

```typescript
const actions = [
  { label: 'عرض',  permission: 'hr.employees.read',   onClick: () => router.push(`/employees/${id}`) },
  { label: 'تعديل', permission: 'hr.employees.update', onClick: () => openSheet(id) },
  { label: 'حذف',  permission: 'hr.employees.delete',  onClick: () => openConfirm(id), destructive: true },
].filter(({ permission }) => can(permission));
```

### 4.6 Forbidden Permission Patterns

```typescript
// NEVER — role-name checks
if (user.role === 'admin') { ... }

// NEVER — reading arrays directly in components
if (permissions.includes('hr.employees.read')) { ... }
// use useCan() instead — it checks deniedPermissions too

// NEVER — trusting frontend permissions for destructive operations
// Always let the backend validate — frontend checks are UI-only
```

