```

### 6.3 Salary Display

Backend returns salary as string — always parse before display:

```typescript
new Intl.NumberFormat('ar-SA', { style: 'currency', currency: 'SAR' })
  .format(parseFloat(row.original.baseSalary))
```

### 6.4 Pagination — Always Server-side

Sync pagination state with URL:

```typescript
const [page, setPage] = useQueryState('page', parseAsInteger.withDefault(1));
const [limit] = useQueryState('limit', parseAsInteger.withDefault(200));
```

### 6.5 Forbidden Table Patterns

```typescript
// NEVER — client-side filter of server data
const filtered = items.filter(e => e.nameAr.includes(search));

// NEVER — raw HTML tables
<table><tr><td>...</td></tr></table>

// NEVER — adding sort UI without confirming backend supports it
// Sorting is hardcoded per endpoint — verify first
```

