## 8. Architecture Rules

### 8.1 Feature Structure

Every feature follows this structure — no exceptions:

```
src/features/{module}/
  services/        {module}.service.ts       — all API calls
  schemas/         {form}.schema.ts          — Zod schemas + types
  components/      {Module}Columns.tsx       — table columns
                   {Action}{Entity}Form.tsx  — forms
                   {Module}Table.tsx         — table wrapper
  hooks/           use{Module}.ts            — custom hooks (optional)
  types/           {module}.types.ts         — TypeScript types
```

### 8.2 Component Rules

- Maximum 300 lines per component — split if larger
- Server Components by default — add `'use client'` only when needed
- `'use client'` is required for: `useQuery`, `useMutation`, `useState`, `useForm`, event handlers
- Never put business logic inside page files — delegate to feature components

### 8.3 What Is NOT Implemented

Do not build UI for these — they do not exist on the backend yet:

- Leave requests (create / approve flow)
- Attendance records and logs
- File or avatar upload
- WebSocket / real-time notifications
- Hijri calendar
- Refresh token / token renewal UI

If a task requires one of these, stop and ask before building.

