## 9. Error Handling

### 9.1 API Errors

```typescript
// Always handle in onError of useMutation
onError: (err: ApiErrorResponse) => {
  const details = err.error?.details;
  const message = Array.isArray(details)
    ? details.join('، ')
    : (details ?? err.message ?? 'حدث خطأ غير متوقع');
  toast.error(message);
}
```

### 9.2 Validation Errors

Backend returns status `400` with `error.details` as `string[]`.
Display inline via React Hook Form `setError` or as a toast — not both.

### 9.3 Unauthorized (401)

Redirect to login. Clear auth store.

### 9.4 Forbidden (403)

Show `/unauthorized` page. Do not show a toast.

